00:48:18,786 --> 00:48:20,720
Danish customs.
Have you anything to declare?

875
00:48:20,888 --> 00:48:23,379
No.
Madame? Thank you.

876
00:48:23,557 --> 00:48:25,081
Madame Anderson.

877
00:48:25,259 --> 00:48:27,727
Madame Anderson!
Oh, yes!

878
00:48:27,895 --> 00:48:29,556
Boynin. Everything in order?

879
00:48:29,730 --> 00:48:30,924
Yes. It seems to be.

880
00:48:31,098 --> 00:48:33,157
Welcome to Denmark.
I hope you enjoy your visit.

881
00:48:33,333 --> 00:48:36,325
Thank you.

882
00:48:37,304 --> 00:48:40,273
I'm sorry. I forgot.
I've had so many names.

883
00:48:40,441 --> 00:48:41,806
It was a struggle to get you that one.

884
00:48:41,975 --> 00:48:43,272
Why Aanderson?

885
00:48:43,444 --> 00:48:45,241
Oh, well, you needed some name,

886
00:48:45,412 --> 00:48:46,811
And once, I was in a situation with...

887
00:48:46,980 --> 00:48:48,641
With a lady?

888
00:48:48,816 --> 00:48:50,875
Well, as an alias,
it is innocuous enough.

889
00:48:51,051 --> 00:48:53,349
"Madame A. Anderson."

890
00:48:53,520 --> 00:48:55,010
The least real thing about me

891
00:48:55,189 --> 00:48:56,451
Is my legal reality.

892
00:48:56,623 --> 00:48:58,318
What happened to
the other Madame Anderson?

893
00:48:58,492 --> 00:48:59,891
Oh, nothing very important.

894
00:49:00,060 --> 00:49:02,551
You just got tired of her?

895
00:49:02,729 --> 00:49:05,254
This visa is good for only 14 days.

896
00:49:05,432 --> 00:49:06,592
Two weeks.

897
00:49:06,767 --> 00:49:09,429
Most people have a lifetime
in which to be accepted.

898
00:49:09,603 --> 00:49:10,934
Suppose two weeks are not enough?

899
00:49:11,105 --> 00:49:14,097
They must be.

900
00:49:58,719 --> 00:49:59,651
What's that for?

